{
  "mcpServers": {
    "MCP_DOCKER": {
      "url": "http://host.docker.internal:8811/mcp",
      "transport": "streamable-http",
      "description": "Docker MCP Toolkit Gateway - Remote HTTP connection. Run gateway on HOST with: docker mcp gateway run --transport streaming --port 8811"
    }
  }
}

{
  "mcpServers": {
    "hackerdogs-mcp-server": {
      "url": "http://preview.hackerdogs.ai/mcp/",
      "headers": {
        "Authorization": "Bearer YOUR_HACKERDOGS_API_KEY"
      },
      "_comment": "URL must end with /. Direct dev: http://192.168.5.15/mcp/ (Caddy). Production: https://preview.hackerdogs.ai/mcp/",
      "transport": "streamable-http"
    }
  }
}

Description:
A comprehensive network and domain analysis toolkit for AI assistants. It provides a suite of tools for DNS exploration (A, AAAA, MX, TXT records), WHOIS registration lookups, and deep connectivity testing. Notable features include TLS certificate chain analysis and "HTTP Ping," which breaks down response times into specific stages: DNS resolution, TCP connection, TLS handshake, and Time to First Byte (TTFB).

Search Keywords: DNS lookup tool, WHOIS query, TLS certificate checker, HTTP response timing, TTFB analysis, connectivity testing, network diagnostics, RFC 8484 DNS-over-HTTPS.

Use Case: Diagnosing a slow website by asking the AI to "perform an HTTP ping on example.com and identify if the delay is in the DNS resolution or the TLS handshake."

mcp-netutils is a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server providing comprehensive network and domain analysis capabilities for AI assistants. It enables AI models to perform DNS lookups, WHOIS queries, connectivity testing, TLS certificate analysis, HTTP endpoint monitoring, and hostname resolution.

For local DNS queries, it uses the system's configured DNS servers. For remote DNS queries, it uses Cloudflare DNS-over-HTTPS queries with a fallback to Google DNS-over-HTTPS. This is more than enough for most use cases.

For custom DNS-over-HTTPS servers, you can use the --remote-server-address flag. The server endpoint must implement the HTTP response format as defined by RFC 8484.

For custom WHOIS servers, you can use the --custom-whois-server flag. The server endpoint must implement the HTTP response format as defined by RFC 3912, although plain text responses are also supported.

Local DNS Queries: Perform DNS lookups using the OS-configured DNS servers
Remote DNS-over-HTTPS: Perform secure DNS queries via Cloudflare and Google DNS-over-HTTPS services
WHOIS Lookups: Perform WHOIS queries to get domain registration information
Hostname Resolution: Convert hostnames to their corresponding IP addresses (IPv4, IPv6, or both)
Ping Operations: Test connectivity and measure response times to hosts using ICMP
HTTP Ping Operations: Test HTTP endpoints and measure detailed response times including DNS, connection, TLS, and TTFB timing
TLS Certificate Analysis: Check TLS certificate chains for validity, expiration, and detailed certificate information
Multiple Record Types: Support for A, AAAA, CNAME, MX, NS, PTR, SOA, SRV, and TXT record types
Fallback Mechanism: Automatically tries multiple DNS servers for reliable results
SSE Support: Run as an HTTP server with Server-Sent Events (SSE) for web-based integrations

{
  "mcpServers": {
    "netutils": {
      "command": "docker",
      "args": [
        "run",
        "-i",
        "--rm",
        "ghcr.io/patrickdappollonio/mcp-netutils:latest",
        // Add custom options if needed:
        // "--remote-server-address=https://your-custom-doh-server.com/dns-query",
        // "--custom-whois-server=whois.yourdomain.com",
        // "--timeout=5s",
        // "--ping-timeout=5s",
        // "--ping-count=4",
        // "--http-ping-timeout=10s",
        // "--http-ping-count=1",
        // "--tls-timeout=10s"
      ],
      "env": {}
    }
  }
}

Configuration:
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "ocr": {
      "args": [
        "run",
        "--rm",
        "-i",
        "--env",
        "PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1",
        "hackerdogs/hackerdogs-mcp-ocr:latest"
      ],
      "command": "docker",
      "description": "MCP OCR Server - Extract text from images using Tesseract OCR. Supports local files, URLs, and image bytes. Dynamically built Docker image from mcp-ocr PyPI package."
    }
  }
}

{
  "mcpServers": {
    "pdf-reader": {
      "args": [
        "run",
        "--rm",
        "-i",
        "--env",
        "NODE_ENV=production",
        "--env",
        "PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1",
        "hackerdogs/hackerdogs-mcp-pdf-reader-sylphx:latest"
      ],
      "command": "docker",
      "description": "MCP PDF Reader Server - Extract text from PDF files using @sylphx/pdf-reader-mcp. Supports PDF URLs via sources array. Dynamically built Docker image from npm package."
